{"ts":"2026-05-05T03:58:42.646Z","turn":1,"input":"look around","position":[0,0],"narrative":"The air is cold and smells of damp earth and pine needles. Before you stands a rough-hewn wooden door, dark with age and scarred by weather. To your left, a narrow path winds into dense shadow where the trees press close together. A faint sound, like dripping water, echoes from deeper within the woods. A pile of dry, brittle leaves lies scattered at your feet.\n\nYou can open the wooden door, or follow the shadowed path to the left."}
{"ts":"2026-05-05T03:58:58.965Z","turn":2,"input":"north","position":[1,0],"narrative":"The ground beneath your boots crunches over dry shale as you move north. The air grows noticeably colder, carrying the sharp, resinous scent of pine and damp earth. After a few minutes of walking, you arrive at a narrow ravine. To the west, a thin ribbon of smoke drifts lazily over the ridge, confirming the fire is indeed distant. Across the ravine, a set of worn, uneven stone steps leads up toward a thicket of stunted black oaks."}
{"ts":"2026-05-05T04:01:17.006Z","turn":3,"input":"go to the black oaks","position":[1,0],"narrative":"The dry shale scrapes beneath your boots as you ascend the stone steps. The air immediately grows heavier, smelling sharply of damp earth and decaying pine needles as you enter the thicket of black oaks. The silence here is profound, broken only by the faint rustling of unseen creatures in the shadows. As you push past the lowest branches, you notice that the smoke drifting from the west seems thicker here, clinging to the undersides of the heavy boughs. A narrow, dark path winds deeper into the thicket just ahead."}
{"ts":"2026-05-05T04:02:03.132Z","turn":4,"input":"Follow the path","position":[1,0],"narrative":"The dry shale crunches under your boots as you descend from the stone steps and enter the thicket. The air immediately grows colder, the scent of pine sharp and biting. The narrow path is choked with tangled roots and shadow. Ahead, the smoke becomes noticeably denser, swirling thickly around the base of the oldest black oaks. A faint, rhythmic dripping sound echoes from deeper within the woods.\n\nYou can follow the dark path forward into the dense shadows, or attempt to investigate the source of the thickening smoke near the largest oak."}
{"ts":"2026-05-05T04:03:00.673Z","turn":5,"input":"investigate the smoke","position":[1,0],"narrative":"The smoke is dry and acrid, carrying the faint, sweet smell of burning pine. As you approach the largest oak, you notice the thickest smoke clings to the lower boughs, revealing that the air immediately beneath them is noticeably cooler and damper than the rest of the ravine. A faint, rhythmic dripping sound echoes from deeper within the shadows of the trees.\n\nA small, rusted iron lantern lies half-buried in the roots near the base of the oak."}
