{"ts":"2026-05-05T16:08:00.786Z","turn":1,"input":"look around","position":[0,0],"narrative":"The flickering fluorescent lights cast shifting shadows across the cramped carriage. The air smells of stale dust and damp wool. You see four other passengers, all staring fixedly ahead or at their knees, refusing to meet your gaze. On the floor near your feet, the half-empty bottle of plum wine catches the faint light. Directly across the aisle, resting on the window seat, is the leather satchel. The conductor's cap sits starkly on the empty seat at the front. A low, rhythmic groan vibrates through the metal frame of the train as it rattles violently through the dark woods.\n\nA corridor leads down the length of the car; a door stands slightly ajar at the far end."}
